|WKBNAME|000
    query_shield

|WKBSYNOPSIS|000
    |YK0int|000     |CKBquery_shield|000()
    |YK0int|000     |CKBquery_shield|000(|YK0int|000 |GKBiType|000)
    |YK0mapping|000 |CKBquery_shield|000(|YK0-1|000)

|WKBDESCRIPTION|000
    Query a living creature/player's shield. Output changes based on
    argument passed.

    If no argument is passed (or |GKB0|000 is passed), the player's generic
    shield amount is returned.  This shield will block damage, regardless
    of damage type.

    If a valid damage type (see <types.h>) is passed, the specific shield
    amount is returned.  This shield will only block that type of damage.

    If a value less than |GKB0|000 or greater than |GKBALL_DAM_TYPES|000 is passed,
    a mapping in the form of <type>:<shield> is returned.

    |CKBquery_shield|000() is defined in /secure/living.c

|WKBSEE ALSO|000
    |CKBset_shield|000(L), |CKBadd_shield|000(L), |CKBremove_shield|000(L)

